    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p><title render="italic">A History of Michigan in Paintings</title> was a series of paintings commissioned by Michigan Bell Telephone Company to advance the knowledge of the State of Michigan's "colorful and exciting development." Robert Thom was the artist. F. Clever Bald wrote the accompanying text for the graphic reproductions of the paintings.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The prints are illustrative of significant moments in the history of Michigan from pre-history to World War II.</p>
    </scopecontent>
